    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-10-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="446"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 1229/1.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">British Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-10-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 545.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of the 10th instant, expressing the thanks of His Majesty’s
                    Government <pb facs="0683" n="571" xml:id="pg_571"/> for this Government’s
                    action in conditionally waiving its extraterritorial rights in Zanzibar, and to
                    say that this department would be pleased to be advised when the German
                    Government shall have made a similar waiver.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
